you want it to mean.

49:26.931 --> 49:29.631
Don't fool yourself
too much about me.

49:34.637 --> 49:37.673
<i>Hey, there you go.</i>

49:37.675 --> 49:39.007
You look like a million bucks.

49:39.009 --> 49:42.611
<i>Feel better now?</i>

49:42.613 --> 49:45.381
I feel like a hundred bucks.

49:45.383 --> 49:48.517
Come by 'cause I wanted to
talk to you about my job.

49:49.652 --> 49:52.888
I wanna work. I need a job.

49:52.890 --> 49:55.924
My daddy don't care
if he gots a job, but I do.

49:55.926 --> 49:58.894
You'd work in this rain,
wouldn't you?

49:59.896 --> 50:02.431
If you need me to.

50:05.168 --> 50:08.470
Let me slip my shoes on.
I'll run you back home.

50:14.411 --> 50:18.180
Hey, we'll be there
in just a second, okay?

50:19.616 --> 50:21.817
Hey.

50:21.819 --> 50:24.686
You know you don't have to take
no shit from nobody, right?

50:25.722 --> 50:28.023
You know that, right?

50:28.025 --> 50:30.025
Yes, ma'am.

50:30.027 --> 50:34.196
Good. Now let's go.

50:36.900 --> 50:38.834
- How you been, Chris?
- Good, how about you?

50:38.836 --> 50:39.691
Doing all right.

50:39.717 --> 50:42.471
- You still doing the mixed martial arts?
- Yes, sir.

50:42.473 --> 50:44.640
What you doing
out in the rain, Joe?

50:44.642 --> 50:47.743
Oh, I need two pounds of ham

50:47.745 --> 50:50.679
- and a pound of Swiss cheese sliced up.
- All right.

50:50.681 --> 50:51.880
Come on, you get the cheese,
I'll get the ham.

50:51.882 --> 50:56.552
Yes, sir. Looks like every time I get a
little ahead, it starts in raining again.

51:02.792 --> 51:05.994
Here you go.

51:05.996 --> 51:08.163
Well, it's not much. Now look here.

51:08.165 --> 51:10.632
When it dries up,

51:10.634 --> 51:13.068
you come down here early
in the morning, 'fore light,

51:13.070 --> 51:14.956
and I'll pick you up
and take you to work.

51:14.982 --> 51:17.105
We got plenty to do when
the weather gets right.

51:17.107 --> 51:20.242
You got a clock? No, you wouldn't.

51:20.244 --> 51:22.845
All right, I'll find you a
wind-up clock or something.

51:22.847 --> 51:24.146
All right, then.

51:24.148 --> 51:25.747
Thank you, sir.

51:25.749 --> 51:27.749
No, you don't need to call
me "sir" all the time.

51:27.751 --> 51:31.653
I'm your friend, you understand?

51:31.655 --> 51:33.789
All right. Hey, where's his ham?

51:33.791 --> 51:36.158
<i>- Hang on, we're coming.</i>
<i>- All right.</i>

51:56.246 --> 51:58.213
Ahem.

52:09.025 --> 52:12.027
What are you thinking, Joe?

52:14.030 --> 52:16.031
Nothing.

52:17.767 --> 52:21.036
There's nothing I can do,
and I hate it.

52:22.205 --> 52:25.674
That's not true.

52:25.676 --> 52:29.044
Yeah, it is.

52:31.015 --> 52:34.816
<i>You look at me like
I can make a move.</i>

52:34.818 --> 52:37.052
<i>What are you thinking when</i>
<i>you look at me like that?</i>

52:37.054 --> 52:40.722
<i>Don't you care?</i>

52:40.724 --> 52:42.190
<i>I don't know who I am.</i>

52:45.262 --> 52:51.767
<i>But I know what keeps
me alive is restraint.</i>

52:51.769 --> 52:55.003
<i>It keeps me out of jail.</i>

52:55.005 --> 52:57.706
<i>Keeps me from hurting people.</i>

53:04.314 --> 53:07.683
Hey.

53:07.685 --> 53:12.621
<i>The mark of some fucked-up
faith that there is a reason.</i>

53:12.623 --> 53:13.755
Thank you.

53:13.757 --> 53:17.059
<i>A reason for all of this.</i>

53:17.061 --> 53:21.063
<i>A reason in most moments
I shouldn't do what I want to do.</i>

53:23.132 --> 53:26.101
<i>I do as I'm told.</i>

53:28.739 --> 53:32.274
<i>These men who bust their asses</i>
<i>work like dogs.</i>

53:33.876 --> 53:37.946
<i>I believe in them,</i>
<i>but every day, they hurt.</i>

53:39.148 --> 53:42.317
<i>They get old, they peel back.</i>

53:45.321 --> 53:48.624
<i>There's no frontier anymore.</i>

53:48.626 --> 53:50.258
Allan.

53:50.260 --> 53:52.694
Clark.

53:52.696 --> 53:55.097
Gary.

53:55.099 --> 53:58.300
<i>And I watch that boy,</i>

53:58.302 --> 54:01.269
<i>and I see someone</i>
<i>who's nothing like me,</i>

54:01.271 --> 54:06.341
<i>but he's a child</i>
<i>folks left behind...</i>

54:06.343 --> 54:09.778
<i>with no defense.</i>

54:09.780 --> 54:14.016
<i>Balanced right there.</i>

54:15.318 --> 54:17.686
What do you want?

54:22.358 --> 54:28.163
<i>- What is it you want?</i>
<i>- Nothing.</i>

54:31.435 --> 54:34.836
<i>Just tell me what I can do.</i>

54:37.340 --> 54:39.741
<i>I like you.</i>

54:42.211 --> 54:45.280
<i>I like you too, but what's
the point in any of it?</i>

54:51.220 --> 54:54.423
<i>Fuck to this day.</i>

54:54.425 --> 54:57.726
<i>I mean, fuck to this day.</i>

55:01.297 --> 55:06.268
<i>It's all just gonna boil up</i>
<i>and wash us away.</i>

55:11.908 --> 55:14.876
<i>And he'll still be here.</i>

55:18.915 --> 55:20.749
<i>Or maybe he won't.</i>

55:30.960 --> 55:33.995
Damn, Joe, why do you keep loading all
these fools in this little truck?

55:33.997 --> 55:35.430
Good to have you
with us again, Sammy.

55:35.432 --> 55:36.898
You drop down any more,
we're gonna have to

55:36.900 --> 55:38.500
get out and push,
and I ain't pushing shit.

55:38.502 --> 55:40.969
I thought you had your
eye on a new truck, Joe.

55:40.971 --> 55:42.738
I ain't getting no new truck.

55:42.740 --> 55:45.240
- You need one.
- No, I don't.

55:45.242 --> 55:47.776
If you get a new truck, how
much you want for this old one?

55:47.778 --> 55:49.444
You mean this old piece of junk?

55:49.446 --> 55:52.781
Smell like somebody done
died up in there. It's nasty.

55:52.783 --> 55:54.182
I don't mind the smell. I like it.

55:54.184 --> 55:56.084
It smells good to me.

55:56.086 --> 55:58.320
Yeah, but this thing...

55:58.322 --> 56:01.490
I spend as much time working
on it as I do driving it.

56:01.492 --> 56:04.326
'Course there ain't
nothing major wrong with it.

56:04.328 --> 56:06.828
Just little shit. You know,
it needs some brakes.

56:06.830 --> 56:08.964
It needs a new...

56:08.966 --> 56:13.168
Joe, come on.

56:13.170 --> 56:15.036
I'll buy it from you.
I'll work my butt off.

56:15.038 --> 56:17.339
I love the truck. You have
to give it to me now.

56:17.341 --> 56:21.009
Well, I mean, it's got
a lot of miles on it.

56:21.011 --> 56:22.911
You'd be better finding
one in town somewhere.

56:22.913 --> 56:25.380
I don't want one in town.
I like that one.

56:26.916 --> 56:29.818
Come on, Joe.

56:31.053 --> 56:33.922
All right. I'll take $900 for it...

56:33.924 --> 56:35.991
